<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main>
    <div id="about-page">
        <h1 class="section-title">About the Quest Board</h1>
        <div class="divider"></div>

        <p>
            Long before the roads of Hyrule were safe to travel, the Adventurer's Guild raised a
            board in every village square where any soul with a problem could post it, and any
            soul with a sword — or a strong back, or a sharp eye — could answer the call. The
            Hyrule Quest Board carries on that tradition: a place to post quests, take them up,
            and see them through to the end.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-subheading">How the Guild Works</h2>

        <div class="about-roles">
            <article class="about-role-card">
                <h3>Hero</h3>
                <p>
                    Any traveler who registers becomes a Hero. Browse the board, accept a quest,
                    and file a completion report when the deed is done.
                </p>
            </article>
            <article class="about-role-card">
                <h3>Guild Officer</h3>
                <p>
                    Officers read every completion report that comes in, approving the ones that
                    hold up and sending the rest back with notes.
                </p>
            </article>
            <article class="about-role-card">
                <h3>Administrator</h3>
                <p>
                    Administrators keep the board itself in order — posting new quests, managing
                    categories, and overseeing the Guild's membership.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>

        <a href="/quests" class="btn">Browse the Board</a>
    </div>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
